# ============================================================
# .trivyignore — Accepted CVE suppressions for Trivy
# ============================================================
# CVE-2026-22732 — Spring Security: security policy bypass and information
# disclosure (spring-security-web). Fixed in Spring Security 6.5.9 / 7.0.4,
# which require Spring Boot 3.5.x / 4.0.x respectively. The project is
# currently pinned to Spring Boot 3.4.x (Spring Cloud 2024.0.0 compatibility).
# Migration to Spring Boot 3.5.x is planned for the next major dependency
# update cycle. Risk mitigated by network-layer controls (API gateway, no
# direct external exposure of internal services).
CVE-2026-22732
# Format: one CVE-ID per line, with a comment explaining the
# justification — mirrors the approach used in
# config/dependency-check/suppressions.xml for OWASP DC.
#
# Example:
#   # CVE-2024-99999 — not exploitable: affected component (libfoo)
#   # is not reachable in our container configuration.
#   CVE-2024-99999
# ============================================================
